title: China's 10 Inversion Roller Coaster is a head turner
text:
China's 10 Inversion Roller Coaster is a head turner Last updated 10:12, September 29 2015 Theme Park Review 
10 Inversion Roller Coaster POV Chimelong Paradise China 
Tired of doing the same old corkscrew at Rainbow's End? 
Check out this head-spinning, vomit inducing roller coaster found at the Chime-Long Paradise Amusement Park in China. 
Once the only coaster in the world with 10 inversions, it was recently knocked off its perch by two other roller coasters at theme parks in the UK. Screen Grab 
Thrill-seekers enjoy the ride of a lifetime on the 10 inversion roller coaster at China???s Chimelong Paradise Amusement Park. 
Nevertheless, the twirling inversion is enough to make even the hardiest of roller-coaster goers feel sick. 
Would you take a chance on this roller coaster or have you been on better? Tell us in comments below.
